@trekonomics We all grow up with pre-enlightenment values, assuming the world we see as children is how it must be. Learning otherwise requires a combination of good education, good community, good politics, and good therapy.

@trekonomics I remember being disturbed that my mom and my best friend’s mom — the two of them best friends themselves — had differing policies n whether one should play in the yard barefoot or with socks.

@trekonomics Not unrelated to the debate among 17th century rabbis as to whether one should light Hanukkah candles from right to left or vice versa — with the unexamined assumption that there was a right way and a wrong way.
